SoniaEmu - emulate gamepad input on Linux using a mobile device (POC).

This is a monorepo.
For better visibility, install WebUI as a PWA.
This project is designed for local network use only and lacks security features necessary for the over-the-internet deployment.

While this project is intended to be ran and used only on Linux, WebUI can still be ran on other systems, though nothing will happen obviously.

Rust code for this project is a modified version of "arduino-joystick" project by gwilymk:
https://github.com/gwilymk/arduino-joystick

Running:
Run via Docker (the "input" group has to be set up):
    sh gid-setup.sh (or set up manually)
    docker-compose build
    docker-compose up
OR
Run via 2 separate instances on the host machine:
    (in emulator/)
        cargo run <optionally - a custom path to a unix socket>
    (in webui/):
    Create a venv and install requirements using pip or poetry, then:
        python run.py <optional arguments>

Installing WebUI as a PWA:
    Safari: "Share button" -> "Add to Home Screen"
    Chrome: "Menu button" -> "Add to Home Screen"

Demo:
https://jarasiau.github.io/sonia-emu/ 

Data format:
    Data is being sent as a fixed-size packaged struct with three fields:
    prefix, input_id and value
    prefixes are "b" for buttons, and "j" for axes (joysticks and triggers).

Fixes for possible issues:
1. If running into issues with launching the emulator (permission denied):
    Try adding yourself to the input group,
If this doesn't work, create a custom uinput rule:
(In "/etc/udev/rules.d/99-uinput.rules"):
    KERNEL=="uinput", MODE="0660", GROUP="input", OPTIONS+="static_node=uinput"
After that, reload the rules:
    sudo udevadm control --reload-rules
    sudo udevadm trigger --subsystem-match=input
If the issue persists, try deleting your existing uinput device and recreating it with:
    sudo modprobe uinput
    reboot

2. If Steam controls are mixed up:
    Go to steam settings
    Go to "Controller"
    Click on "Begin Test" in "Test Device Inputs"
    Click "Setup Device Inputs"
    Set your inputs up
    Enable Steam Input for generic controllers

3. If running into issues with docker (input group not being detected):
Run "sh gid-setup.sh"
OR
Get the group GID and put it in the .env manually:
    getent group input

4. In order to fix controls being mixed up in The Binding of Isaac:
    Use any other version of Proton but Experimental.
    Enable Steam Input.
